  "text_preview": "\"grade\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► Grade: How to sign \"grade\" in ASL. The concept of \"grade\" can be signed a variety of ways in ASL depending on your meaning and your preferences. Many people prefer to fingerspell \"grade.\" Also, it is common for even skilled signers to use one version of \"grade\" to mean both a \"letter grade\" and \"a grade in school.\" It is not worth arguing about. I'll show you my recommendations but you should sign \"grade\" however your local Deaf sign it. I do encourage you however to think about the roots of each version of the sign. If you mean grade as in \"What grade are you in?\" you can use the version of \"grade\" that puts a \"G\" hand onto the non-dominant palm. You may also touch the \"G\" hand to the palm twice"
}
